'''Tomáš Chorý''' (born 26 January 1995) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==
Chorý joined [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] in the 2018 summer transfer window.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Plzeň má věž za 25 milionů! Chorý se upsal na 4,5 roku, lídr musel připlatit|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2017-18/322819/plzen-ma-vez-za-25-milionu-chory-se-upsal-na-4-5-roku-lidr-musel-priplatit.html|website=[[Blesk]]|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|date=4 January 2018|access-date=21 November 2023|language=cs}}</ref> He scored two goals in a [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League]] group stage match against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Španělský tisk: Plzeň se nikdy nevzdala, Chorý svlékl barcelonskou obranu|url=https://sport.aktualne.cz/fotbal/spanelsky-tisk-plzen-se-nikdy-nevzdala-chory-svlekl-barcelon/r~620a8c085a7911eda25a0cc47ab5f122/|website=Aktualně.cz|date=2 November 2022|access-date=17 June 2024|language=cs|publisher=[[Economia]]}}</ref> Chorý won his second title in the [[2021–22 Czech First League]] on 15 May 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|first1=Zdeněk|last1=Soukup|first2=David|last2=Ako|title=Mistři! Plzeň po čtyřech letech získala fotbalový titul, Slavia skončí druhá|url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/mistri-viktorie-plzen-po-ctyrech-letech-slavi-vyhru-v-nejvyssi-soutezi-20220511.html|website=[[Deník]]|date=11 May 2022|access-date=17 May 2022|language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> In April 2024, he signed a contract with Viktoria Plzeň until 2027.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Viktoria si pojistila kanonýra, Chorý podepsal s Plzní novou smlouvu|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/viktoria-si-pojistila-kanonyra-chory-podepsal-s-plzni-novou-smlouvu/2504970|website=České Noviny|date=12 April 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

On 5 October 2020, Chorý went on loan to Belgian club [[SV Zulte-Waregem|Zulte-Waregem]],<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jonas|last=Withouck|title=Transfer: Zulte Waregem huurt Tsjechische targetspits Tomáš Chorý|url=https://doorfansvoorfans.org/2020/10/05/transfer-zulte-waregem-huurt-tsjechische-targetspits-tomas-chory/|website=Door Fans Voor Fans|date=5 October 2020|access-date=17 June 2024|language=nl}}</ref> scoring four goals at the [[2020–21 Belgian First Division A]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Chorý bude z Plzně hostovat v belgickém Waregemu|url=https://sport.aktualne.cz/fotbal/ceska-liga/chory-bude-z-plzne-hostovat-v-belgickem-waregemu/r~5fc98ae8071a11ebaabd0cc47ab5f122/|website=Aktualně.cz|date=5 October 2020|access-date=17 May 2022|language=cs|publisher=[[Economia]]}}</ref>

On 3 July 2024, Chorý signed a contract with [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] until 30 June 2027.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Novou posilou Slavie je Tomáš Chorý|url=https://www.slavia.cz/article/21984-Novou-posilou-Slavie-je-Tomas-Chory|website=[[SK Slavia Prague]]|date=3 July 2024|access-date=3 July 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

On 7 August 2025, Chorý was banned by the LFA Disciplinary commission for six matches after he hit goalkeeper [[Milan Heča]] to the crotch in the away match against [[1. FC Slovácko|Slovácko]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Bartoloměj|last=Černík|title=Chorý zná trest za úder do rozkroku! Pauza do konce září, derby stihne|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-chance-liga/464869/chory-zna-trest-za-uder-do-rozkroku-pauza-do-konce-zari-derby-stihne.html|website=[[Blesk]]|date=7 August 2025|access-date=7 August 2025|language=cs|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]}}</ref>

On 12 April 2026, in the home goalless draw with Viktoria Plzeň, Chorý received yellow card after a tackle with [[Sampson Dweh]]. The yellow card was changed to a red card after [[Video assistant referee|VAR]] intervention, when Chorý immediately afterwards allegedly spat at Dweh while yelled at him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.aktualne.cz/chory-dostal-za-plivanec-cervenou-slavia-tak-s-plzni-urvala-jen-bod/r~aaa29d4c5b75966f1c6098538fd219b5/|title=Chorý dostal za plivanec červenou, Slavia tak s Plzní urvala jen bod|language=cs|work=Aktuálně.cz|date=12 April 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|publisher=[[Economia]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]}}</ref> Chorý said after the match, that he yelled at Dweh but denied spitting on him. Slavia manager [[Jindřich Trpišovský]] said he did not see any spitting. Slavia filled a complaint in protest against the verdict.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mikeš|first=Pavel|url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/tomas-chory-plivnuti-cervena-karta-vylouceni-slavia-plzen-protest-rozhodci.html|title=Chorého (ne)plivanec: Slavia podává protest. Argumenty? Emoce i fakta|language=cs|work=[[Deník]]|date=13 April 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> On 16 April 2026, Slavia chairman Jaroslav Tvrdík personally defended Chorý in front of the LFA Disciplinary commission.<ref>{{cite news|last=Duffek|first=Dominik|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/slavia-tomas-chory-plivanec-trest-jaroslav-tvrdik.A260416_161712_fotbal_duff|title=Tvrdík o Chorém: Plivnutí nelze dokázat, po trestu je poptávka. Komisi pustil i video|language=cs|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|date=16 April 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref> As a verdict, Chorý was banned for one match, the disciplinary commission stated that they did not see any intentional spitting.<ref>{{cite news|last=Černík|first=Bartoloměj|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-chance-liga/474492/chory-dostal-nejnizsi-mozny-trest-za-plivanec-vynecha-jen-jeden-zapas-co-rekla-komise.html|title=Chorý dostal nejnižší možný trest, za "plivanec" vynechá jen jeden zápas. Co řekla komise?|language=cs|work=[[Blesk]]|date=16 April 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]}}</ref>

On 9 May 2026, Chorý in the [[Prague derby]] received yellow card after he elbowed Sparta defender [[Asger Sørensen]] to the head. The yellow card was changed to a red card after VAR intervention. Slavia chairman Jaroslav Tvrdík said that Chorý cannot control his behavior, have been immediately removed from the first team and would not play for Slavia again.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.aktualne.cz/fotbal/chory-neni-schopen-ovladat-svoje-chovani-takhle-na-hriste-nepatri-prohlasil-tvrdik/r~aaa29ffa446400509ba1cb106b6b53bb/?lp=1|title=Chorý není schopen ovládat svoje chování, takhle na hřiště nepatří, prohlásil Tvrdík|language=cs|work=Aktuálně.cz|date=10 May 2026|access-date=10 May 2026|publisher=[[Economia]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]}}</ref> On 14 May 2026, Chorý was banned by the LFA Disciplinary commission for six matches.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Bartoloměj|last=Černík|title=Tresty pro trio slávistů: OSM zápasů pro Mosese, Chorý dostal šest. Co Douděra?|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-chance-liga/475498/tresty-pro-trio-slavistu-osm-zapasu-pro-mosese-chory-dostal-sest-co-doudera.html|website=[[Blesk]]|date=14 May 2026|access-date=14 May 2026|language=cs|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Chorý debuted for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic senior team]] on 20 November 2023 in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group E]] match against [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]].  In an eventful 3-0 victory Chorý scored a goal, got an assist, and was fouled to earn a Moldovan player his second yellow card to reduce his side to 10 men.<ref>{{cite web|title=Česko 3–0 Moldavsko|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-euro-fotbaliste-v-primem-souboji-o-me-hosti-moldavsko-atmosferu-narusila-afera-5016909|website=Sport.cz|publisher=Borgis|date=20 November 2023|via=Se čtyřmi změnami v základní sestavě proti páteční remíze v Polsku a dvěma debutanty Vitíkem a Chorým|trans-quote=Four changes in the starting line-up against a draw on Friday in Poland, with two debutants Vitík and Chorý.}}</ref>

